  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "In London, you can find **beef jerky** and **biltong** in a variety of places, including specialty stores, supermarkets, and online retailers. Here are some options:\n\n### 1. **Specialty Shops**\n   - **The South African Shop**: Located in Earl's Court, this shop specializes in South African products, including biltong. They also offer online ordering.\n   - **Jerky Corner**: A dedicated store for beef jerky and other dried meat snacks, offering a wide range of flavors and brands.\n   - **The Biltong Co.**: Focused on biltong and dro\u00ebwors, they have stores in London and also deliver across the UK.\n\n### 2. **Supermarkets**\n   - **Waitrose**: Often stocks biltong and beef jerky in the snack or international foods section.\n   - **Tesco**: Sometimes carries biltong and beef jerky in the snack aisle.\n   - **Sainsbury's**: Occasionally stocks biltong, especially in larger stores.\n   - **Marks & Spencer**: Offers premium beef jerky and biltong in their snack range.\n   - **Whole Foods Market**: Known for carrying high-quality biltong and beef jerky.\n\n### 3. **Markets**\n   - **Borough Market**: Some vendors may sell artisanal biltong and beef jerky.\n   - **Old Spitalfields Market**: Occasionally has stalls selling these snacks.\n\n### 4. **Online Retailers**\n   - **Amazon UK**: Offers a wide variety of beef jerky and biltong brands.\n   - **Specialist websites**: Look for dedicated biltong and jerky websites like **BiltongBox**, **The Jerky Company**, or **SnackBrands UK**.\n\n### 5. **South African Restaurants or Cafes**\n   - Many South African restaurants and cafes in London sell biltong and sometimes beef jerky. Check places like **The Springbok** or **SA Kitchen**.\n\n### 6. **Convenience Stores**\n   - Larger convenience stores or petrol stations (like BP or Shell) often stock beef jerky snacks.\n\nIf you're looking for artisanal or high-quality options, specialty shops and online retailers are your best bet. Supermarkets and markets are great for more accessible options.",
